&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team owns the apps that bring Peloton’s world-class workout experience to iOS, tvOS, and watchOS. We build native Swift applications that engage both our connected-hardware members and mobile-only subscribers. As a critical growth engine for Peloton, our apps deliver high-quality fitness content across a wide range of price points.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will collaborate with cross-functional partners to design, build, and scale features that meet our highest quality standards, directly shaping how millions of users interact with the Peloton brand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Daily Impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;End-to-End Feature Development:&lt;/strong&gt; Collaborate with Product, Design, and QA to build, test, and ship engaging features across iOS, iPadOS, tvOS, and watchOS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Architecture &amp;amp; Innovation:&lt;/strong&gt; Participate in architectural discussions and leverage modern frameworks like SwiftUI to build high-performance client-side features.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Ownership &amp;amp; Team Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt; Take ownership of features within a nimble team environment while actively participating in a supportive culture that values mentorship, open feedback, and career growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Bring To Peloton&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; 3+ years of iOS development experience (or equivalent education) shipping apps to a large user base.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Proficiency:&lt;/strong&gt; Strong foundation in SwiftUI, UIKit, MVVM architecture, Git, and RESTful API integrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clean Code Practices:&lt;/strong&gt; A passion for writing readable, maintainable, well-documented, and thoroughly tested code.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication &amp;amp; Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt; Ability to effectively translate UX/UI requirements into code and communicate complex technical solutions or trade-offs to both engineering peers and non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with device-centric frameworks such as CoreLocation, CoreMotion, or hardware integrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
