&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Director of IT Operations &amp;amp; Digital Resilience will be the primary architect of our internal technology experience and operational stability. You will lead a global team of 20+ professionals across Service Desk, Infrastructure, SRE, and Compliance functions. Your mission is to ensure a seamless &quot;always-on&quot; employee experience while maintaining a rigorous security and compliance posture across our global footprint.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOUR DAILY IMPACT AT PELOTON&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct the global IT Helpdesk and a specialized VIP Support tier, ensuring white-glove service for executive leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead end-point management strategy (MDM, imaging, lifecycle) to ensure employees have the right tools, whether remote or in-office&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary advocate for the &quot;Employee Experience,&quot; using technology to reduce friction in the daily workflow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee global network architecture, ensuring high-availability for local, remote, and hybrid connectivity solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage SRE and Incident Management frameworks to minimize downtime and ensure rapid recovery from system failures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the global network stack, ensuring seamless VPN, SD-WAN, and office-based connectivity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the functional lead for IT regulatory compliance (SOX, GDPR, SOC2) and cybersecurity governance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee Loss Prevention strategies to mitigate hardware theft, data leakage, and unauthorized access&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align operational workflows with corporate security policies to ensure &quot;security by design&quot; in IT Ops&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage offshore vendor relationships (BPO/MSP), ensuring third-party delivery meets internal quality and security standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a multi-million dollar budget encompassing hardware, software licensing, and managed service contracts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will be responsible for the design and weekly delivery of the&amp;nbsp;IT Operational Command Dashboard, including:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MTTR (Mean Time to Resolve), First-Call Resolution, and CSAT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SLOs/SLAs for core infrastructure and network uptime&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Audit readiness status and Loss Prevention recovery rates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOU BRING TO PELOTON&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12+ years in IT Operations, with at least 5 years in a senior leadership role managing multi-disciplinary teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep familiarity with ITIL frameworks, SRE principles, and modern GRC tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of managing a team of 20+, including remote and offshore resources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to translate complex technical &quot;uptime&quot; data into business-centric &quot;experience&quot; reports for the C-Suite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: &#39;Helvetica Neue&#39;;&quot;&gt;#LI-DD1&lt;br&gt;#LI-Hybrid&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;The base salary range represents the low and high end of the anticipated salary range for this position based at our New York City headquarters. The actual base salary offered for this position will depend on numerous factors including, without limitation, experience and business objectives and if the location for the job changes. Our base salary is just one component of Peloton’s competitive total rewards strategy that also includes annual

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT PELOTON&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Peloton, We empower people to live fit, strong, long, and happy lives. We use technology and world-class instruction to connect the world through fitness, empowering people to be the best version of themselves anywhere, anytime. We&#39;re a team of talented and passionate individuals who are committed to innovation and creating exceptional user experiences. We are seeking a highly motivated and skilled Senior Electrical Engineer to join our Hardware Engineering team and contribute to the next generation of connected fitness products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOUR DAILY IMPACT AT PELOTON&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and develop electrical systems and circuits for new and existing Peloton products, including consumer electronics, motor controls, power supplies, and sensor integration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct rigorous testing and validation of electrical designs to ensure they meet performance, reliability, and safety standards (e.g., UL, CE, FCC). This involves debugging hardware, analyzing test data, and implementing design changes as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with cross-functional teams, including mechanical engineering, firmware, software, and industrial design, to integrate electrical systems seamlessly into the final product&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with our manufacturing partners to ensure designs are manufacturable, and provide support during production ramp-up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current with emerging technologies and industry trends to drive innovation and continuous improvement in our products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOU BRING TO PELOTON&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Bachelor&#39;s degree in Electrical Engineering or a related field. A Master&#39;s degree is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in electrical engineering, with a strong background in power systems, power supplies, and consumer electronics development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of power systems, AC and DC motors, and line-connected appliance designs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience in both internal and joint development work, working with overseas JDM and CM partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of regulatory requirements, including design for UL and CE safety and EMC requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with schematic capture and PCB layout tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with microcontroller-based system design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with lab equipment, such as oscilloscopes, multimeters, spectrum analyzers, and motor test equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This role requires 4–6 trips annually, involving both domestic and international travel to Asia and Mexico&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and collaboration abilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and handle multiple projects simultaneously in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;The base salary range represents the low and high end of the anticipated salary range for this position based at our Woodinville, WA headquarters. The actual base salary offered for this position will depend on numerous factors including, without limitation, experience and business objectives and if the location for the job changes. Our base salary is just one component of Peloton’s competitive total rewards strategy that also includes annual equity awards and an Employee Stock Purchase Plan as well as other region-specific health and welfare benefits.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;As an organization, one of our top priorities is to maintai

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SENIOR FULL STACK SOFTWARE ENGINEER, DEVICE SERVICES&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Senior Full Stack Software Engineer - a strong front end/back end developer - to join our team. You will be working within an agile scrum team and building Device Management features to support every Peloton Connected Fitness Device. You are a hybrid API/web developer who is comfortable moving back and forth between the front and back end.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are someone who thinks about simplicity and works to provide solutions that reduce the complexity across services. You are team-focused and prioritize collective learning in addition to solving problems. You build collective ownership amongst the team by contributing to code reviews, designs, whiteboarding, and pair-programming.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOUR DAILY IMPACT AT PELOTON:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on different technologies across API and the Web within an agile development environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for iterating on the process, technology, and communication with peer engineers, designers, and product managers on a daily basis to scope, develop and deliver a software experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a technical leader within the team you work with and within Peloton in general. Able to identify common patterns as well as develop and foster development of reusable components and standards across teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate technical projects across teams within Peloton&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a valued member of an autonomous, multi-functional agile team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOU BRING TO PELOTON&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of software engineering experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Python, Kotlin, Javascript/Typescript or similar languages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in at least one JavaScript framework like React (preferred), Vue, or similar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building, testing, and scaling out RESTful microservices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with accessing, querying and writing to data stores like PostgreSQL, MongoDB, DynamoDB, Elasticsearch, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiar with deployment toolings/environments such as Kubernetes, Terraform, GitHub Actions, Jenkins etc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with android development ecosystem or Site Reliability Engineering is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Claude or similar models and AI development tools is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT PELOTON:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Peloton (NASDAQ: PTON) provides Members with expert instruction, and world class content to create impactful and entertaining workout experiences for anyone, anywhere and at any stage in their fitness journey. At home, outdoors, traveling, or at the gym, Peloton brings together innovative hardware, distinctive software, and exclusive content. Founded in 2012 and headquartered in New York City, Peloton has millions of Members across the US, UK, Canada, Germany, Australia, and Austria. For more information, visit www.onepeloton.com.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Peloton is an equal opportunity employer and complies with all applicable federal, state, and local fair employment practices laws. Equal employment opportunity has been, and will continue to be, a fundamental principle at Peloton, where all team members, applicants, and other covered persons are considered on the basis of their personal capabilities and qualifications without discrimination because of race, color, religion, sex, age, national origin, disability, pregnancy, genetic information, military or veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, marital and civil partnership/union statu

&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Peloton&#39;s Content Department is a collaborative and forward-thinking team dedicated to delivering world-class subscription content to our members every day. As a Senior Media Operations Technician, you will play a critical hands-on role in the execution and support of Media and post-production operations for our global content pipeline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be deeply embedded in media management, content management, quality control (QC), and delivery workflows, serving as a key connector between pre-production, production, post-production, and final distribution. This position is ideal for someone who excels at keeping complex content pipelines running smoothly, possesses a strong technical post-production skill set, and enjoys partnering across teams in a dynamic, high-volume environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOUR DAILY IMPACT AT PELOTON&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively manage and contribute to all stages of post-production workflows, from ingest through final delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, troubleshoot, and resolve issues in On-Demand and Banked Content to maintain content quality and publishing standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform hands-on editing, audio mastering, graphics integration, and color correction across a wide range of deliverables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review content from rough cut to final file delivery, providing quality-control feedback at multiple stages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute media QC, ensuring that assets meet Peloton’s technical specifications, file naming conventions, and organizational standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize, catalog, and maintain media assets across platforms and content management databases (CMS and MAM systems)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle direct file deliveries and manage asset movement, supporting seamless distribution to stakeholders and platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Production, Post-Production teams, and Vendors to ensure timelines, technical needs, and deliverables are met&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to continuous improvement efforts by providing workflow insights and suggesting operational efficiencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Address and manage post-production support requests from Content, Production, and Product teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOU BRING TO PELOTON&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Over 4 years experience managing end-to-end post-production or Media Operations workflows in a professional media/broadcast environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to manage video editing, audio mixing, motion graphics, and color correction with a high degree of ownership and accountability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep familiarity with media QC practices, technical standards, codecs, frame rates, color spaces, and delivery pipelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with industry-standard tools such as Adobe Creative Suite (Premiere, After Effects, Photoshop, Lightroom), DaVinci Resolve, or Pro Tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Project Management Tools (such as Asana)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with content management systems (CMS) and media asset management (MAM) platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational skills, attention to detail, and the ability to prioritize steady streams of media assets effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong cross-functional communication skills to work collaboratively with Production, Creative, and Product teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously, meeting deadlines through effective self-management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work a shift-based schedule to support our global content timeline, which will include scheduled early mornings, evenings, holidays and weekends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of naming conventions, metadata tagging, and media archival best practices&lt;
